text: Rinata Sultanova (born 17 March 1998) is a Kazakh road and track cyclist. She competed at the 2020 UCI Track Cycling Championship, and 2021 UCI Track Cycling Championship. She was national champion at the 2021 Kazakhistan National Time Trial Championships. She won the silver medal at the 2020 Asian Track Cycling Championship. == References == == Other websites == * Rinata Sultanova of Kazakhstan lies injured after the crash, Getty Images Category:1988 births
